<span style='float: right; width: 280px; height: 187px; margin: 0 0 5px 5px; border: 1px solid black;'><script type='text/javascript'>flash_object ('http://graphics.millsberry.com/buddy/buddy_featured.swf', '280', '187', 'userName=bre922&buddyTimeStamp=20060123&buddyScriptURL=http%3A%2F%2Fmillsberry.com%2Fbuddy%2Fprocess_buddy.phtml&unixTimeStamp=1193059772&serverTimeOffset=28800', '', 'exactfit', 'transparent');</script></span>
Meet <b>Hazel</b>, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Hazel lives at <a href='/home/?user=bre922'>66019 Strawberry Way</a> in one of the elegant historic homes of Ravenwood.  Hazel has been working on redecorating and renovating her antique home since July 25, 2005, and she's almost gotten it just right.<br><br>Ever since she started attending <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/academy/">Millsberry Academy</a>, Hazel has taken part in every show that the school's theatre group has put on.  Because she's so flexible as an actress, Hazel can take on any role and make it her own, from the Witch in "Hansel and Gretel" to the lead role in "Cinderella."  Hazel also has a quick wit that allows her to improvise whenever the need arises onstage.  As any of her schoolmates could tell you, this clever girl never fails to get the audience laughing when she delivers a comical story or a joke.<br><br>In addition to helping her on the stage, Hazel's outgoing nature has also enabled her to make friends all over town.  After school and on weekends, Hazel can often be found at a mall, browsing the shops with her friends, or at her best friend's house, going over the lines of their next theatre production.  Hazel's favorite hangout, however, is the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/theater.phtml">movie theater</a> at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a>.  She loves films and tries to go to the movies as often as possible, because she thinks it's a good way to learn about acting.  In the rare moments when Hazel has some time alone, she usually spends it drawing.  Hazel's drawings are rather vibrant, just like her personality, with bold shades of pink, green, and orange.<br><br>Acting and drawing aren't Hazel's only ways of expressing herself, though.  She also loves to sing and recently wrote some tunes of her own.  Hazel's songs have a very energetic style, with fast, upbeat rhythms, just like her favorite types of music (rap, pop, and punk).  Almost as soon as Hazel produced her songs at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/studio/">Millsberry Recording Studio</a>, people all over town were dancing to them.  Her tracks were so popular, in fact, that one of them soon made it to the top of the Cinnamon Toast Crunch Top Ten chart!<br><br>Thanks for being a good citizen, Hazel, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
